## Running the Server

### Development

```bash
dart run bin/main.dart
APP_ENV=dev dart run bin/main.dart

# via CLI (hot-reload on file changes):
dartapi run
dartapi run --watch
dartapi run --env=dev --port=3000
```

### Staging / UAT

```bash
APP_ENV=staging dart run bin/main.dart
APP_ENV=uat    dart run bin/main.dart
```

### Production — native binary (recommended)

```bash
# Compile once:
dartapi build
# or manually:
dart compile exe bin/main.dart -o {{projectName}}

# Run:
APP_ENV=production \
  DB_HOST=db.example.com \
  DB_PASSWORD=secret \
  JWT_ACCESS_SECRET=$(openssl rand -hex 32) \
  JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=$(openssl rand -hex 32) \
  ./{{projectName}}
```

### Multi-core (use all CPU cores)

```bash
dartapi run --isolates=4
# or via env var:
ISOLATES=4 dart run bin/main.dart
```

Each isolate binds to the same port (`shared: true`). The OS load-balances
incoming connections across all isolates.

### Docker

```bash
# Build image (multi-stage: compiles AOT, copies binary to slim runtime):
docker build -t {{projectName}} .

# Run:
docker run -p 8080:8080 \
  -e APP_ENV=production \
  -e DB_HOST=host.docker.internal \
  -e DB_PASSWORD=secret \
  -e JWT_ACCESS_SECRET=<32-char-secret> \
  -e JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=<32-char-secret> \
  {{projectName}}
```

