## API Reference

### Authentication

All protected endpoints require a Bearer token in the `Authorization` header:

```
Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
```

#### `POST /auth/login`

```json
// Request
{ "username": "admin@example.com", "password": "password" }

// Response 200
{
  "accessToken":  "<jwt>",
  "refreshToken": "<jwt>"
}
```

#### `POST /auth/refresh`

```json
// Request
{ "refreshToken": "<refresh_jwt>" }

// Response 200
{
  "accessToken":  "<new_jwt>",
  "refreshToken": "<same_refresh_jwt>"
}
```

#### `POST /auth/logout` *(Bearer token required)*

Revokes the access token immediately. Returns `204 No Content`.

---

### Users *(Bearer token required)*

#### `GET /users`

Returns a paginated list of users.

Query params: `?page=1&limit=20` (limit max 100)

```json
// Response 200
{
  "data": [
    { "id": 1, "name": "Alice", "age": 30, "email": "alice@example.com" }
  ],
  "meta": { "page": 1, "limit": 20, "count": 1 }
}
```

#### `GET /users/<id>`

```json
// Response 200
{ "id": 1, "name": "Alice", "age": 30, "email": "alice@example.com" }

// Response 404
{ "error": "User not found", "statusCode": 404 }
```

#### `POST /users`

All fields are validated. The response includes every validation error when present.

```json
// Request
{ "name": "Carol", "age": 28, "email": "carol@example.com" }

// Response 201
{ "id": 3, "name": "Carol", "age": 28, "email": "carol@example.com" }

// Response 422 (validation failed)
{
  "error": "Validation failed",
  "statusCode": 422,
  "details": ["email: invalid email format", "age: must be between 0 and 150"]
}
```

#### `PUT /users/<id>`

Replaces all fields. Returns `404` if not found.

```json
// Request
{ "name": "Carol Updated", "age": 29, "email": "carol_new@example.com" }

// Response 200
{ "id": 3, "name": "Carol Updated", "age": 29, "email": "carol_new@example.com" }
```

#### `DELETE /users/<id>`

Returns `204 No Content` on success, `404` if not found.

