### Products *(Bearer token required)*

The `GET /products` list is **cached for 5 minutes** per unique URL (including query params).
Look for the `X-Cache: HIT` / `X-Cache: MISS` response header.

#### `GET /products`

```json
// Response 200
{
  "data": [
    { "id": 1, "name": "Widget", "price": 9.99, "quantity": 100 }
  ],
  "meta": { "page": 1, "limit": 20, "count": 1 }
}
```

#### `GET /products/<id>`

```json
{ "id": 1, "name": "Widget", "price": 9.99, "quantity": 100 }
```

#### `POST /products`

Fires a background task after the `201` response is delivered — replace the
placeholder with real notification logic (webhook, email, audit log, etc.).

```json
// Request
{ "name": "Gadget", "price": 49.99, "quantity": 50 }

// Response 201
{ "id": 2, "name": "Gadget", "price": 49.99, "quantity": 50 }
```

#### `PUT /products/<id>`

```json
// Request
{ "name": "Gadget Pro", "price": 59.99, "quantity": 45 }

// Response 200
{ "id": 2, "name": "Gadget Pro", "price": 59.99, "quantity": 45 }
```

#### `DELETE /products/<id>`

Returns `204 No Content` on success, `404` if not found.

