## Middleware Pipeline

Requests pass through middleware in this order (outermost → innermost):

```
requestIdMiddleware        → attaches X-Request-Id header
globalExceptionMiddleware  → catches all unhandled exceptions
rateLimitMiddleware        → 429 if IP exceeds rate limit
timeoutMiddleware          → 503 if handler takes too long
backgroundTaskMiddleware   → enables post-response async tasks
loggingMiddleware          → logs method, path, status, duration
corsMiddleware             → adds CORS headers
compressionMiddleware      → Gzip responses > 1 KB
metricsMiddleware          → tracks Prometheus counters/histograms
router                     ← innermost — dispatches to controllers
```

Per-route cache middleware wraps individual routes (not the global pipeline).

